{{IPAchar|/ɕau/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɕɔː/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɕoː/}}

From {{der|ja|ltc|sort=しよう|-}} {{ltc-l|笙}}. The ''[[呉音#Japanese|goon]]'' reading, so likely the original reading as first borrowed from {{cog|ltc|-}}. Compare modern {{cog|cmn|笙|tr=shēng}}.

The ''shō'' was developed from the Chinese ''{{ll|zh|笙|shēng}}'' that was introduced to Japan during the {{w|Nara period}}.

